<h1>Why MTP Group is Among the Best Fulfillment Operators in Ukraine</h1>
<div class="post-hero-line"></div>
<div class="post-hero-meta">March 10, 2025 &middot; 8 min read</div>
</section>

<!-- ARTICLE -->
<article class="post-body">
<div class="post-body-inner">

<h2>A Decade of Fulfillment Excellence</h2>
<p>When MTP Group opened its first warehouse near Kyiv in 2014, the Ukrainian e-commerce market was still in its infancy. Fulfillment as a service barely existed &mdash; most online store owners packed orders in their living rooms and drove to the post office every afternoon. Over the following decade, MTP Group grew into one of the most recognized third-party logistics providers in the country, now operating two modern warehouses in Shchaslive (2,800 m²) and Bilohorodka (1,100 m²) with a combined capacity of 6,000 shipments per day.</p>
<p>But capacity alone does not make a fulfillment operator great. What sets MTP Group apart is the combination of infrastructure, technology, operational discipline, and a client-first culture that has been refined across more than ten years and 150 active partnerships. In this article, we explore the specific differentiators that place MTP Group among the best fulfillment operators in Ukraine today.</p>

<h2>Infrastructure Built for Resilience</h2>
<p>The foundation of any fulfillment operation is the physical infrastructure. MTP Group's two warehouses total over 4,000 square meters of organized storage space, featuring climate-controlled zones for temperature-sensitive products, dedicated areas for oversized and heavy goods, and a systematic shelving layout optimized for fast picking.</p>
<p>Each facility is equipped with industrial generators capable of sustaining full operations during power outages &mdash; a critical capability in wartime Ukraine. Additionally, both warehouses maintain redundant internet connections through separate providers, ensuring that the warehouse management system (WMS) remains online even when one network goes down. This dual-redundancy approach means that MTP Group has maintained a 99.7% uptime record since February 2022, processing orders without interruption through rolling blackouts and infrastructure attacks.</p>
<p>Security is another infrastructure priority. Both facilities use 24/7 CCTV surveillance, access-controlled entry points, and comprehensive insurance coverage for stored inventory. Clients receive real-time camera access to their designated storage zones upon request.</p>

<h2>Proprietary Technology Stack</h2>
<p>Technology is where MTP Group truly separates itself from competitors. The company operates a proprietary warehouse management system that has been developed and refined internally over the past seven years. Unlike off-the-shelf WMS solutions, this system is specifically designed for the realities of Ukrainian e-commerce: integration with Nova Poshta, Ukrposhta, and Meest carrier APIs, support for Ukrainian CRM platforms like KeyCRM and SalesDrive, and compatibility with popular e-commerce engines including Shopify, WooCommerce, Horoshop, and OpenCart.</p>
<p>The WMS automates the entire order lifecycle. When a customer places an order on a client's online store, the system receives the order within seconds via API, generates a picking list, assigns it to a warehouse operator, and creates the carrier shipping label &mdash; all without any manual intervention. This level of automation reduces the average order processing time to under 12 minutes from receipt to carrier handoff.</p>
<p>Clients access a real-time dashboard that shows current inventory levels by SKU, order processing status, shipping tracking numbers, and return statistics. The dashboard also generates automated alerts when stock levels fall below configurable thresholds, enabling proactive replenishment planning.</p>

<h2>Nova Poshta Top-50 Partner Status</h2>
<p>Carrier relationships directly impact both cost and delivery speed. MTP Group holds top-50 partner status with Nova Poshta, Ukraine's dominant parcel carrier handling over 80% of e-commerce deliveries. This status provides several tangible advantages for clients.</p>
<p>First, MTP Group accesses volume-discounted shipping rates that are significantly lower than what individual online stores can negotiate on their own. These savings are passed directly to clients. Second, Nova Poshta assigns dedicated pickup windows to top-tier partners, meaning parcels leave the warehouse on a predictable schedule rather than waiting for available capacity. Third, claim resolution for lost or damaged parcels is prioritized, with average resolution times of 3-5 business days compared to the standard 10-15 days.</p>

<h2>Client Success Stories</h2>
<h3>Fashion brand scaling from 80 to 1,200 orders per day</h3>
<p>One of MTP Group's most dramatic success stories involves a Ukrainian fashion brand that joined in 2020 with approximately 80 orders per day. The brand's founder was spending six hours daily on logistics and had hired three full-time warehouse employees. After transitioning to MTP Group, the founder redirected all logistics time into marketing and product development. Within eighteen months, daily order volume grew to 1,200 &mdash; a 15x increase &mdash; while the brand's logistics team shrank to zero. The founder now spends roughly six hours per month reviewing fulfillment dashboards.</p>

<h3>Electronics retailer reducing return processing time by 70%</h3>
<p>An electronics retailer struggled with return processing. Returned items sat in boxes for weeks before being inspected, tested, and restocked. After partnering with MTP Group, the return processing cycle dropped from an average of 14 days to just 4 days. The faster turnaround meant that returned items re-entered available inventory sooner, reducing dead stock costs and improving cash flow by an estimated 22% annually.</p>

<h3>Cosmetics startup launching with zero logistics staff</h3>
<p>A cosmetics startup that launched in 2023 chose MTP Group as its fulfillment partner from day one. The founders never hired logistics staff, never rented warehouse space, and never purchased packing equipment. They sent their first batch of products directly from the manufacturer to MTP Group's Shchaslyve warehouse. Within the first year, the startup grew from zero to 400 daily shipments, validating the model of building an e-commerce business entirely on outsourced fulfillment infrastructure.</p>

<h2>Operational Discipline and Quality Control</h2>
<p>Processing thousands of orders daily requires rigorous quality control systems. MTP Group implements a multi-stage verification process: barcode scanning at every touchpoint (receiving, shelving, picking, packing, and carrier handoff), weight-check validation to catch picking errors before parcels leave the warehouse, and random quality audits on 5% of all outgoing shipments each day.</p>
<p>The result is a documented order accuracy rate of 99.6% &mdash; meaning fewer than 4 in every 1,000 orders contain an error. For context, the industry average in Ukraine is estimated at 97-98%, making MTP Group's performance significantly above the norm.</p>
<p>Staff training is another differentiator. New warehouse team members undergo a structured five-day training program before handling live orders. This includes WMS system operation, carrier-specific labeling requirements, fragile item handling protocols, and brand-specific packing instructions for each client. Seasonal workers hired during peak periods complete an accelerated three-day version of the same program.</p>

<h2>Transparent Pricing and No Hidden Fees</h2>
<p>One common frustration among e-commerce businesses evaluating fulfillment providers is opaque pricing. MTP Group addresses this with a fully transparent pricing model published on its website. Clients see exactly what they pay for: receiving per unit, storage per cubic meter per month, picking and packing per order, and carrier shipping at discounted rates. There are no setup fees, no minimum commitment periods, and no hidden charges for standard services like barcode labeling or basic packing materials.</p>
<p>The pricing model is also dynamic: per-shipment costs decrease as monthly volume increases. This means that as a client's business grows, their unit economics improve automatically. For clients shipping over 100 orders per day, MTP Group provides custom pricing proposals tailored to their specific product characteristics and volume projections.</p>

<h2>Continuous Improvement Culture</h2>
<p>What truly defines a best-in-class fulfillment operator is not just current performance but the commitment to getting better. MTP Group conducts quarterly operational reviews with every client, analyzing key performance indicators and identifying areas for optimization. The company reinvests a significant portion of revenue into infrastructure upgrades, technology development, and staff training each year.</p>
<p>Recent investments include expansion of the Bilohorodka facility, implementation of a new barcode scanning system that reduced picking errors by 30%, and development of an enhanced client dashboard with predictive analytics for demand forecasting. These ongoing improvements ensure that MTP Group's service quality continues to advance alongside the growing expectations of the Ukrainian e-commerce market.</p>
<p>For online store owners evaluating fulfillment partners, the message is clear: choosing an operator is not just about today's capacity, but about partnering with a company that will grow and improve alongside your business. With over a decade of proven performance, cutting-edge technology, and a relentless focus on client success, MTP Group has earned its place among the best fulfillment operators in Ukraine.</p>

